## Action: 2026-05-20 (Fix config reload command, multi-PID lookup, and silence CLI usage)
Action: Resolved `./mls config reload` failure when multiple `mls serve` processes are active (e.g., manual serve and background launchd daemon) by enhancing the PID lookup logic (`findMLSServePIDs`) to safely extract, parse, and signal all running process instances. Additionally, set `SilenceUsage: true` on `rootCmd` to globally suppress confusing Cobra usage menus on runtime/operational failures, keeping command outputs clean and focused on actual error messages.

## Action: 2026-05-20 (Fix SIGHUP signal channel race and termination)
Action: Resolved a race condition where receiving a SIGHUP signal (dynamic configuration reload) in the foreground or background `serve` process caused it to exit unexpectedly instead of hot-reloading. The issue was due to both the main thread blocking on `<-sigChan` and the signal-processing background goroutine reading from the same channel, causing them to compete. Fixed this by introducing a dedicated `doneChan` channel so that only the background goroutine reads from `sigChan` and handles `SIGHUP` safely, notifying the main thread only on termination signals (`SIGINT` or `SIGTERM`).

## Action: 2026-05-20 (Enforce single-instance mls serve with cross-platform locking)
Action: Designed and implemented robust, cross-platform single-instance process execution for `mls serve`. Created `internal/utils/lock_unix.go` (leveraging standard `syscall.Flock` on macOS and Linux) and `internal/utils/lock_windows.go` (exclusive-file fallback for Windows compile compatibility). Integrated the locking mechanism at the start of `serveCmd` in `cmd/serve.go` to acquire an exclusive lock on `~/Library/Caches/mls/mls.pid` containing the current process PID. If another instance is already running and holds the lock, the new process prints a helpful notice detailing the active PID and exits cleanly with status 0.

## Action: 2026-05-20 (Cross-platform config open and reveal support)
Action: Extended `mls config open` and `mls config reveal` to operate natively across macOS, Linux, and Windows. Implemented `OpenPath` and `RevealPath` helper functions in `internal/utils/helpers.go` using a clean switch statement on `runtime.GOOS`. `OpenPath` delegates to `open` (macOS), `cmd /c start` (Windows), and `xdg-open` (Linux). `RevealPath` leverages `open -R` (macOS), `explorer /select` (Windows), and opening the parent directory using `xdg-open` (Linux) to guarantee clean native file-manager highlights. Refactored `cmd/config.go` to use these helpers.

