## Action: 2026-05-20 (Cross-platform config reload implementation)
Action: Designed and implemented a robust, fully cross-platform configuration reload mechanism. Introduced a reload signal file (`reload.signal` under local cache directory) touched by `mls config reload`. Refactored `cmd/serve.go` to periodically check (every 2 seconds) the signal file's modification time to reload Viper configuration dynamically across macOS, Linux, and Windows. Created `cmd/reload_unix.go` and `cmd/reload_windows.go` with build tags to handle platform-specific signal subscriptions (`syscall.SIGHUP` on Unix, no-op on Windows) without failing compilation on Windows.
Files updated/created:
- [NEW] cmd/reload_unix.go: Unix-specific signaling (SIGHUP subscription and process lookup).
- [NEW] cmd/reload_windows.go: Windows-specific compile-safe signaling.
- cmd/config.go: Refactored `reloadCmd` to update the signal file and invoke cross-platform signaling.
- cmd/serve.go: Updated signaling loop to monitor both standard OS signals and `reload.signal` modification times.
- README.md: Marked `mls config reload` as fully cross-platform.
Verified: All compilation and race test validations passed.

